Commentary Text: Chakaravarthy to Hetmyer, no ball, there is a long-on, there is a deep mid-wicket, but Hetmyer's backed himself to slog it over. Alas. This one's a little too full, and thus ends up getting dragged off the inside half of the one-legged heave. And that's not even the best part, with Gill - at long-on - judging the dip perfectly, running, diving in front, low, clean. No, wait, more drama. They're checking the no ball, and Chakaravarthy's front foot is right by the edge of the crease. Just outside rules the third umpire. Well well. Hetmyer's already sitting in the dugout, and he has a life ..

Pant knows just one way, and he came out with just one plan -- to swing crazily at everything. So he steps out, looks to pull across the line, and ends up with a top-edge as far as mid-off.
